HEADWORD: Discourteous
<hw>Dis*cour"te*ous</hw> <pr>(?; see <er>Courteous</er>, 277)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>dis-</ets> + <ets>courteous</ets>: cf.
OF. <ets>discortois</ets>.]</ety> <def>Uncivil; rude; wanting in
courtesy or good manners; uncourteous.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Dis*cour"te*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Dis*cour"te*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

